1
00:00:58,461 --> 00:01:00,730
Previously on Dating Alys Perez.

2
00:01:00,755 --> 00:01:02,757
You still love me, don't you, Alys?

3
00:01:02,882 --> 00:01:04,383
I don't love you anymore!

4
00:01:04,681 --> 00:01:05,765
Hi, Silly!

5
00:01:06,282 --> 00:01:07,278
Tripp!

6
00:01:07,303 --> 00:01:08,846
I saw Tripp yesterday.

7
00:01:09,096 --> 00:01:10,138
My god, Alys.

8
00:01:10,139 --> 00:01:12,640
He's gotten even more handsome.

9
00:01:12,641 --> 00:01:13,664
Okay, kiss!

10
00:01:14,310 --> 00:01:15,477
I missed you too!

11
00:01:15,478 --> 00:01:17,104
Okay, kiss Auntie Alys, too!

12
00:01:17,855 --> 00:01:18,855
No!

13
00:01:18,939 --> 00:01:20,107
We have a problem.

14
00:01:20,191 --> 00:01:21,316
Our wedding planner

15
00:01:21,317 --> 00:01:22,193
cancelled.

16
00:01:22,194 --> 00:01:23,736
Can you please step up for us?

17
00:01:23,986 --> 00:01:25,028
Cristine's gone.

18
00:01:25,029 --> 00:01:27,114
It's you and me again, Alys.

19
00:01:27,323 --> 00:01:28,741
Make your groom happy.

20
00:01:28,866 --> 00:01:30,117
You ready?

21
00:01:53,390 --> 00:01:54,683
Good morning, Ms. Alys!

22
00:01:55,101 --> 00:01:56,352
Good morning, Charmaine.

23
00:01:56,477 --> 00:01:57,686
Is Mommy still abroad?

24
00:01:57,770 --> 00:01:58,979
Yes, Ma'am.

25
00:02:05,611 --> 00:02:07,279
God please help me.

26
00:02:07,488 --> 00:02:09,031
Yes, Ma'am? Sorry?

27
00:02:09,281 --> 00:02:11,283
Oh, nothing.
Never mind.

28
00:02:15,579 --> 00:02:16,789
No, thanks.

29
00:02:17,331 --> 00:02:19,083
Is this really necessary, Drake?

30
00:02:20,126 --> 00:02:21,877
Good morning to you, too, Alys.

31
00:02:23,568 --> 00:02:24,610
Come on.

32
00:02:24,887 --> 00:02:26,639
Cristine and I aren't the same size.

33
00:02:28,685 --> 00:02:30,521
Are you calling yourself fat?

34
00:02:31,683 --> 00:02:32,893
Excuse me?!

35
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:35,570
What did you say?

36
00:02:36,649 --> 00:02:37,900
Take that back.

37
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:51,656
How dare he call me fat?

38
00:02:51,657 --> 00:02:52,991
Where's Ms. Stinson's gown?

39
00:02:52,992 --> 00:02:54,160
Here, Ms. Perez.

40
00:02:54,577 --> 00:02:55,202
This one.

41
00:02:55,536 --> 00:02:56,579
We'll see who's fat.

42
00:02:56,954 --> 00:02:59,373
If this really fits me,
you're in trouble!

43
00:03:00,875 --> 00:03:01,916
One...

44
00:03:01,917 --> 00:03:02,710
Two...

45
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:03,710
Three!

46
00:03:04,503 --> 00:03:06,422
Ms. Alys, the gown might get damaged!

47
00:03:06,839 --> 00:03:07,923
Shut up!

48
00:03:08,215 --> 00:03:09,465
On the count of three,
you're gonna zip it up.

49
00:03:09,466 --> 00:03:12,177
No matter what happens,
even if it gets torn, I don't care!

50
00:03:12,178 --> 00:03:13,458
Yes, Ma'am. Understood.

51
00:03:13,723 --> 00:03:14,471
Okay?!

52
00:03:14,472 --> 00:03:16,015
- Okay, Ma'am!
- One more try.

53
00:03:16,223 --> 00:03:17,266
One...

54
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,600
Two...

55
00:03:18,601 --> 00:03:19,601
Three!

56
00:03:22,002 --> 00:03:23,170
Are we good?

57
00:03:23,195 --> 00:03:24,738
Yes, Ma'am. It fits!

58
00:03:27,026 --> 00:03:28,026
It fits!

59
00:03:38,829 --> 00:03:42,374
I really am Dana Ferrer
and Cyriel Perez's daughter.

60
00:03:43,876 --> 00:03:45,543
He called me fat?

61
00:03:45,544 --> 00:03:47,213
Who's fat now?

62
00:03:47,755 --> 00:03:49,423
I'll show you, Drake Palma.

63
00:03:52,301 --> 00:03:56,262
I'm very sorry, Sir.
But you may not see the bride.

64
00:03:56,263 --> 00:03:59,015
Don't you believe the superstition?

65
00:03:59,016 --> 00:04:01,518
The girl in that gown is Alys Perez.

66
00:04:02,269 --> 00:04:03,229
If we were getting married,

67
00:04:03,230 --> 00:04:05,981
do you think I'll let anyone stop me?

68
00:04:06,857 --> 00:04:08,358
What marriage?

69
00:04:08,359 --> 00:04:09,610
This guy's got some nerve.

70
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:11,110
But, Sir...

71
00:04:14,406 --> 00:04:16,075
Excuse me, can you
leave us for a moment?

72
00:04:16,408 --> 00:04:17,408
Yes, Ma'am.

73
00:04:17,952 --> 00:04:18,952
Thank you.

74
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:44,269
Same...

75
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:44,937
old...

76
00:04:45,187 --> 00:04:46,187
Alys.

77
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:48,565
Huh?

78
00:04:48,565 --> 00:04:49,565
That's it?

79
00:04:49,858 --> 00:04:53,194
I could barely breathe
just to fit into Cristine's gown.

80
00:04:53,195 --> 00:04:54,612
And that's all he said?

81
00:04:54,613 --> 00:04:56,115
Same old Alys?

82
00:04:58,033 --> 00:04:59,535
So?

83
00:05:00,452 --> 00:05:02,413
Where's the next destination?

84
00:05:03,122 --> 00:05:04,498
Drake, what are we doing here?

85
00:05:09,295 --> 00:05:10,421
What are we doing, Alys?

86
00:05:11,171 --> 00:05:13,674
Why the hell is
everything so confusing?

87
00:05:13,924 --> 00:05:15,133
Ever since I met Drake,

88
00:05:15,134 --> 00:05:17,219
“Complicated” became my middle name.

89
00:05:18,387 --> 00:05:19,430
Fuck off, Drake!

90
00:05:25,394 --> 00:05:26,478
Yes, Drake.

91
00:05:27,229 --> 00:05:28,564
This is who I am.

92
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:32,443
I'm not the same old
Alys that you left years ago.

93
00:05:33,152 --> 00:05:34,778
You left me, remember?

94
00:05:34,903 --> 00:05:36,946
You left me to freakin’ grow up.

95
00:05:36,947 --> 00:05:38,531
Now, I curse.

96
00:05:38,532 --> 00:05:41,076
I drink —
Hell, I even gamble if I want to.

97
00:05:41,660 --> 00:05:42,952
Look at me.

98
00:05:42,953 --> 00:05:44,038
I grew up.

99
00:05:44,455 --> 00:05:46,957
And I don't want to be
with you any longer.

100
00:05:47,207 --> 00:05:49,083
So, please, please...

101
00:05:49,084 --> 00:05:50,878
Leave me alone!

102
00:05:51,045 --> 00:05:52,545
Please don't start where we left off,

103
00:05:52,546 --> 00:05:54,882
because I don't want
to start over with you.

104
00:05:55,716 --> 00:05:58,468
I want to continue
living my life as it is.

105
00:05:58,469 --> 00:05:59,720
Peacefully.

106
00:06:00,012 --> 00:06:02,139
I can take whatever
you give me, Alys.

107
00:06:03,223 --> 00:06:05,768
But don't underestimate
how I feel about you.

108
00:06:06,060 --> 00:06:07,811
Childish or not, you're still Alys...

109
00:06:09,063 --> 00:06:10,397
I don't want to be with you!

110
00:06:11,398 --> 00:06:13,108
What the hell is
fucking wrong with you?

111
00:06:14,234 --> 00:06:15,735
Are you fucking obsessed with me?

112
00:06:15,736 --> 00:06:17,654
You're getting married to Cristine!

113
00:06:18,489 --> 00:06:19,489
Are you insane?!

114
00:06:19,615 --> 00:06:21,867
I still have time to back out, Alys.

115
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:58,319
Please!

116
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:01,323
Drake!

117
00:07:02,825 --> 00:07:06,494
Drink and forget.

118
00:07:06,495 --> 00:07:08,330
Drink until you forget.

119
00:07:13,085 --> 00:07:14,920
Can you feel that?

120
00:07:15,587 --> 00:07:18,799
That's the heartbeat of a man
who's obsessed with you.

121
00:07:19,091 --> 00:07:20,426
Throw me a bone, Alys.

122
00:07:20,556 --> 00:07:22,975
I'll pick it up for you,
no matter what.

123
00:07:24,805 --> 00:07:26,098
I'm yours, Alys.

124
00:07:26,677 --> 00:07:27,970
So, deal with it.

125
00:07:29,356 --> 00:07:31,036
All the complications are coming back.

126
00:07:31,061 --> 00:07:33,272
And I really don't quite like it.

127
00:07:34,648 --> 00:07:37,066
Tonight, I'm coming clean.

128
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:39,352
I don't want to fight with Tripp.

129
00:07:39,377 --> 00:07:41,087
I can't lose him.

130
00:07:41,112 --> 00:07:43,197
Hell, I don't want to lose him.

131
00:07:45,672 --> 00:07:48,132
I gave your heart back
a long time ago, Drake.

132
00:07:48,226 --> 00:07:50,145
Find anyone else but me!

133
00:07:50,664 --> 00:07:52,499
You won't get anything
from me anymore.

134
00:07:52,655 --> 00:07:54,491
I'm happy with you, Alys.

135
00:07:55,009 --> 00:07:56,040
So, I'll stay.

136
00:08:00,507 --> 00:08:01,507
You...

137
00:08:02,342 --> 00:08:03,594
disgust me!

138
00:10:19,563 --> 00:10:21,147
Manang, where is Tripp?

139
00:10:21,148 --> 00:10:22,733
In his office, Ma'am.

140
00:10:32,576 --> 00:10:34,327
Hey!

141
00:10:34,328 --> 00:10:36,158
Are we getting married now, Perez?

142
00:10:37,164 --> 00:10:38,706
Ha ha ha.

143
00:10:38,707 --> 00:10:40,667
Very funny.

144
00:10:42,210 --> 00:10:43,838
What's with the wedding gown?

145
00:10:47,301 --> 00:10:48,469
Let me guess.

146
00:10:49,187 --> 00:10:50,275
Runaway Bride?

147
00:10:51,976 --> 00:10:52,977
I told you,

148
00:10:53,596 --> 00:10:55,097
stop watching too many movies?

149
00:10:58,695 --> 00:10:59,695
Tripp...

150
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:02,980
What's wrong?

151
00:11:07,027 --> 00:11:09,654
Well, I'm wearing a wedding gown.

152
00:11:09,655 --> 00:11:11,353
And you look decent enough.

153
00:11:12,949 --> 00:11:14,682
The only thing missing is the ring.

154
00:11:16,521 --> 00:11:18,397
Are you proposing to me, Perez?

155
00:11:41,478 --> 00:11:43,688
I'll have to speak to Uncle Cyriel first.

156
00:11:43,689 --> 00:11:44,689
Okay?

157
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,092
Slow down.

158
00:11:46,525 --> 00:11:47,553
Wow.

159
00:11:47,818 --> 00:11:48,818
Slow down.

160
00:11:49,464 --> 00:11:51,257
Big words coming from you.

161
00:11:53,508 --> 00:11:55,009
I will propose one day.

162
00:11:55,691 --> 00:11:56,901
Just chill.

163
00:11:58,101 --> 00:11:59,519
We'll get there someday.

164
00:12:00,497 --> 00:12:01,497
Okay?

165
00:12:04,594 --> 00:12:06,388
Why are you wearing a wedding dress?

166
00:12:07,571 --> 00:12:08,738
No reason.

167
00:12:08,763 --> 00:12:09,973
Just a little preview for you.

168
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:12,516
I look pretty, right?

169
00:12:18,765 --> 00:12:19,862
Fine.

170
00:12:20,475 --> 00:12:21,518
You are pretty.

171
00:12:21,893 --> 00:12:24,167
Wow, that sounded so forced.

172
00:12:25,696 --> 00:12:26,696
It’s not.

173
00:12:28,707 --> 00:12:30,208
You're too beautiful.

174
00:12:32,154 --> 00:12:33,947
More than too much.

175
00:12:43,373 --> 00:12:45,500
Why do I feel so guilty?

176
00:12:46,923 --> 00:12:48,268
This isn't right.

177
00:12:51,548 --> 00:12:52,971
Marco!

178
00:12:54,384 --> 00:12:55,776
You kept this?

179
00:12:56,303 --> 00:12:57,463
Of course.

180
00:12:58,013 --> 00:12:59,013
Cute!

181
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:10,471
You know,

182
00:13:11,610 --> 00:13:13,159
if Dad sees us like this,

183
00:13:14,149 --> 00:13:15,315
he might get the wrong idea.

184
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:18,021
Yeah, right.

185
00:13:18,046 --> 00:13:19,798
As if, Marco.

186
00:13:23,079 --> 00:13:24,831
So, why were you wearing
a wedding dress?

187
00:13:32,179 --> 00:13:33,389
You want the truth?

188
00:13:34,502 --> 00:13:35,502
Yes, the truth.

189
00:13:37,072 --> 00:13:39,450
I don't want us to fight, but...

190
00:13:39,638 --> 00:13:42,182
It's better that he hears it from me
than from someone else.

191
00:13:48,939 --> 00:13:50,588
Marco, it's...

192
00:13:50,941 --> 00:13:51,963
It's Drake.

193
00:14:09,321 --> 00:14:10,321
And?

194
00:14:11,104 --> 00:14:12,104
What is it?

195
00:14:16,009 --> 00:14:17,767
I'm sorry, Marco.

196
00:14:19,219 --> 00:14:21,595
Drake is Cristine's groom.

197
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:25,458
I promise I never intended
to keep it from you, but.

198
00:14:25,871 --> 00:14:28,157
I didn't want us to fight.

199
00:14:29,771 --> 00:14:31,243
Please don't be mad.

200
00:14:34,609 --> 00:14:36,173
I'm sorry.

201
00:14:44,369 --> 00:14:45,537
I trust you.

202
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:48,594
You do?

203
00:14:49,157 --> 00:14:50,199
Really?

204
00:14:58,466 --> 00:15:01,177
I trust you so much, Alys.

205
00:15:02,178 --> 00:15:03,915
Even if I don't trust Drake.

206
00:15:10,741 --> 00:15:13,478
So, you and Drake aren't
going to talk anymore?

207
00:15:22,386 --> 00:15:24,680
Two years, Alys.

208
00:15:26,411 --> 00:15:28,163
In those two years,

209
00:15:28,994 --> 00:15:30,704
did I ever make a move?

210
00:15:33,097 --> 00:15:34,118
I didn't, right?

211
00:15:36,814 --> 00:15:38,524
In those two years,

212
00:15:40,318 --> 00:15:41,603
I waited

213
00:15:42,127 --> 00:15:43,545
before I courted you.

214
00:15:44,249 --> 00:15:45,650
And now he says

215
00:15:46,139 --> 00:15:47,599
that I took you away?

216
00:15:50,518 --> 00:15:51,518
So, no.

217
00:15:52,689 --> 00:15:53,837
We're not speaking.

218
00:15:56,524 --> 00:15:57,548
Okay.

219
00:15:58,013 --> 00:15:59,384
I understand.

220
00:16:00,086 --> 00:16:01,353
Come on, don't frown.

221
00:16:02,197 --> 00:16:03,406
Smile.

222
00:16:04,075 --> 00:16:07,037
Come on, smile.
Like that, smile with teeth.

223
00:16:07,062 --> 00:16:08,980
Come on, smile with teeth.

224
00:16:16,753 --> 00:16:18,345
I love you, Marco.

225
00:16:18,773 --> 00:16:20,087
I love you, Zy.

226
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:27,222
It’s happening.

227
00:16:27,675 --> 00:16:29,969
This is exactly what I’m afraid of.

228
00:16:30,141 --> 00:16:32,102
Drake is coming back.

229
00:16:46,522 --> 00:16:47,857
Thank you, nanny.

230
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:50,593
Please prepare an affogato for later.

231
00:16:50,704 --> 00:16:51,538
Okay po, Ma’am.

232
00:16:51,663 --> 00:16:52,706
Thank you.

233
00:17:39,419 --> 00:17:41,028
Marco...

234
00:17:41,463 --> 00:17:42,588
Hmm?

235
00:17:42,589 --> 00:17:43,739
It's hot!

236
00:17:45,842 --> 00:17:47,801
The food you’re cooking, or...

237
00:17:48,428 --> 00:17:49,845
you?

238
00:17:49,846 --> 00:17:51,264
Marco...

239
00:17:53,349 --> 00:17:55,018
- What?
- Marco!

240
00:17:56,425 --> 00:17:57,843
I just missed you.

241
00:17:59,540 --> 00:18:02,341
It's only been a few minutes
since we last saw each other.

242
00:18:05,787 --> 00:18:07,075
That's the thing.

243
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:12,460
You're so stubborn!
Go over there for now!

244
00:18:14,162 --> 00:18:16,239
I’ll stay here, please.

245
00:18:18,024 --> 00:18:21,152
I can't concentrate on cooking like this
if you’ll stay here.

246
00:18:21,177 --> 00:18:22,966
Do you want to eat burnt steak?

247
00:18:26,007 --> 00:18:27,008
Come on, go ahead.

248
00:18:27,033 --> 00:18:28,952
I'll call you when I'm done, okay?

249
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:33,710
There, good boy.

250
00:18:33,735 --> 00:18:36,196
Yes, your Majesty.

251
00:18:36,893 --> 00:18:37,977
Hey, Silly.

252
00:19:18,768 --> 00:19:22,272
This is the invitation to
their annual family reunion.

253
00:19:29,612 --> 00:19:30,697
Oh my gosh!

254
00:19:30,738 --> 00:19:31,406
My god!

255
00:19:31,407 --> 00:19:32,534
What do you have there?

256
00:19:36,369 --> 00:19:37,745
Why are you still hiding it?

257
00:19:37,844 --> 00:19:39,012
I already saw it.

258
00:19:39,534 --> 00:19:43,162
Didn't I tell you that I'd call
you when food is ready?

259
00:19:44,544 --> 00:19:46,920
When the food is ready?

260
00:19:46,921 --> 00:19:48,338
- Marco!
- Is the food ready?

261
00:19:48,339 --> 00:19:49,090
Behave yourself!

262
00:19:49,091 --> 00:19:50,257
Are you sure?

263
00:19:50,258 --> 00:19:51,170
Tripp!

264
00:19:51,298 --> 00:19:52,883
- Stop that!
- Why?

265
00:19:52,969 --> 00:19:53,928
I'm not doing anything.

266
00:19:53,929 --> 00:19:55,053
What is it?

267
00:19:55,054 --> 00:19:55,680
Oh!

268
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:56,680
The food is ready?

269
00:19:57,390 --> 00:19:58,390
Hey!

270
00:20:06,274 --> 00:20:07,525
Will you go with me?

271
00:20:08,366 --> 00:20:09,366
Huh?

272
00:20:09,947 --> 00:20:11,115
I said...

273
00:20:11,532 --> 00:20:13,451
Will you be my date
for the reunion?

274
00:20:14,399 --> 00:20:16,485
I thought you didn't want me to go.

275
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:18,850
Well,

276
00:20:19,177 --> 00:20:21,304
you've already seen Drake so...

277
00:20:21,792 --> 00:20:23,836
I don't think there's
a reason not to go.

278
00:20:24,497 --> 00:20:26,933
I thought you didn't
want to talk to Drake.

279
00:20:28,838 --> 00:20:29,839
I don't.

280
00:20:31,507 --> 00:20:34,509
But, it's not like I can avoid it.

281
00:20:34,510 --> 00:20:35,510
He's my cousin.

282
00:20:36,012 --> 00:20:37,180
That's true.

283
00:20:39,849 --> 00:20:41,017
So?

284
00:20:42,042 --> 00:20:43,623
What do you mean, so?

285
00:20:44,229 --> 00:20:45,355
Is that a yes?

286
00:20:48,564 --> 00:20:49,589
Bless you.

287
00:20:51,903 --> 00:20:53,238
Take some medicine.

288
00:20:53,508 --> 00:20:54,843
Before it gets worse.

289
00:20:55,406 --> 00:20:56,908
No, I'll be fine.

290
00:20:57,033 --> 00:20:59,077
It's probably all the
pepper on the steak.

291
00:21:00,119 --> 00:21:01,119
Hey!

292
00:21:01,746 --> 00:21:03,872
- All the pepper?
- I'm sorry. Excuse me.

293
00:21:03,873 --> 00:21:05,541
You're blaming the pepper now?

294
00:21:05,792 --> 00:21:06,959
Okay, let's go.

295
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,628
Let’s just eat.

296
00:21:09,087 --> 00:21:11,255
Come on, Silly.
Let's get some food.

297
00:21:11,256 --> 00:21:12,715
But I don't want to.

298
00:21:13,091 --> 00:21:14,550
Just eat, will you?

299
00:21:23,017 --> 00:21:24,476
Sick.

300
00:21:24,477 --> 00:21:27,271
Can't come reunion.

301
00:21:27,272 --> 00:21:28,272
Sleep.

302
00:22:04,060 --> 00:22:06,089
No, it's cold.

303
00:22:07,924 --> 00:22:09,019
Drake?

304
00:22:10,718 --> 00:22:12,345
You're not well, Alys Perez.

305
00:22:14,203 --> 00:22:17,165
Of all the things I hate,
is you looking weak.

306
00:22:18,237 --> 00:22:19,456
Don't you know that?

307
00:22:20,616 --> 00:22:21,743
Of course, you don’t.

308
00:22:22,005 --> 00:22:23,423
Who am I to you, anyway?

309
00:22:26,873 --> 00:22:27,957
Oh, right.

310
00:22:29,383 --> 00:22:32,845
This will be the only chance
I have for you to listen.

311
00:22:34,130 --> 00:22:37,394
Because every time I say something,
you always pick a fight with me.

312
00:22:39,220 --> 00:22:41,292
Why are you being
so stubborn, Alys?

313
00:22:42,426 --> 00:22:45,339
Are you mad at me because
of what happened in New York?

314
00:22:46,691 --> 00:22:48,448
I really want to say yes.

315
00:22:48,858 --> 00:22:50,777
I really want to know why he left.

316
00:22:50,802 --> 00:22:52,553
But there's also this part of me

317
00:22:52,672 --> 00:22:54,173
that doesn't want to know.

318
00:22:55,056 --> 00:22:56,515
Don't listen, Alys.

319
00:22:56,540 --> 00:22:57,790
You're happy now.

320
00:22:57,815 --> 00:22:59,941
Do not listen to a word he says.

321
00:22:59,989 --> 00:23:02,449
He will just ruin everything.

322
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:04,058
Like what he did to you before.

323
00:23:04,986 --> 00:23:06,628
Do you really want to know?

324
00:23:08,963 --> 00:23:10,277
Ask me, Alys.

325
00:23:13,758 --> 00:23:15,635
I just hope you won't get mad

326
00:23:16,221 --> 00:23:19,480
that I didn't tell you why I left you.

327
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:45,943
Alys!

328
00:23:49,205 --> 00:23:50,456
What's wrong with you?

329
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:55,860
I'm so stupid.

330
00:23:57,255 --> 00:23:58,172
Oh, well.

331
00:23:58,173 --> 00:23:59,382
What's done is done.

332
00:24:00,948 --> 00:24:01,967
Here.

333
00:24:02,301 --> 00:24:03,301
Eat.

334
00:24:05,930 --> 00:24:06,973
Porridge?

335
00:24:08,099 --> 00:24:09,307
Don't be picky.

336
00:24:09,308 --> 00:24:10,977
Do I look like I know
how to cook?

337
00:24:11,894 --> 00:24:13,812
Who asked you to do the cooking?

338
00:24:13,813 --> 00:24:15,857
We have the nannies for that.

339
00:24:16,901 --> 00:24:18,068
"Thanks, Dane!"

340
00:24:18,093 --> 00:24:19,094
"Best brother ever."

341
00:24:21,093 --> 00:24:23,304
Thank you, Baby Dane!

342
00:24:23,531 --> 00:24:24,298
Stop!

343
00:24:24,323 --> 00:24:25,323
Quit it.

344
00:24:28,523 --> 00:24:29,940
This little brat.

345
00:24:29,965 --> 00:24:33,093
He acts like he's four years
older than me.

346
00:24:37,628 --> 00:24:39,380
This is pretty sweet though.

347
00:24:44,802 --> 00:24:46,471
Tastes fine.

348
00:24:50,266 --> 00:24:51,934
Ask me, Alys.

349
00:24:52,727 --> 00:24:54,604
I just hope you won't get mad

350
00:24:55,229 --> 00:24:59,025
that I didn't tell you why I left you.

351
00:25:03,054 --> 00:25:04,113
Seriously,

352
00:25:04,906 --> 00:25:06,991
do I really have to ask him?

353
00:25:07,950 --> 00:25:08,988
What's wrong with me?

354
00:25:10,161 --> 00:25:11,746
I'm happy with my life.

355
00:25:13,039 --> 00:25:17,042
Do I really have to
complicate things again?

356
00:25:17,043 --> 00:25:18,460
Bestie!

357
00:25:18,461 --> 00:25:20,338
Who are you talking to?

358
00:25:21,422 --> 00:25:22,422
No one.

359
00:25:22,632 --> 00:25:23,883
I'm just talking to myself.

360
00:25:25,053 --> 00:25:26,512
Aunt Dana said you’re sick.

361
00:25:30,431 --> 00:25:31,512
I see.

362
00:25:31,565 --> 00:25:33,150
So, you're staying in?

363
00:25:35,311 --> 00:25:37,021
Great!
Let's do a movie marathon!

364
00:25:42,943 --> 00:25:44,535
I have a better idea!

365
00:25:44,946 --> 00:25:46,531
Tell me everything.

366
00:25:48,282 --> 00:25:49,282
About what?

367
00:25:49,348 --> 00:25:50,432
About Drake!

368
00:25:50,457 --> 00:25:51,791
Come on, come on!

369
00:25:52,570 --> 00:25:54,154
What's with you, Aya?

370
00:25:54,179 --> 00:25:55,824
What do you think
my life is with Drake?

371
00:25:55,849 --> 00:25:56,975
A soap opera?

372
00:25:57,088 --> 00:25:59,488
Do I have to update you
on every little thing?

373
00:26:00,621 --> 00:26:01,962
Come on, Bestie.

374
00:26:01,963 --> 00:26:04,098
I was just a little curious.

375
00:26:04,632 --> 00:26:07,760
If they push through with
their wedding next week,

376
00:26:08,594 --> 00:26:10,676
does that mean...

377
00:26:11,764 --> 00:26:13,683
it's really game over for DrAlys?

378
00:26:17,905 --> 00:26:19,448
Ouch!

379
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:24,544
Aya Pineda, you're such a gossip!

380
00:26:24,569 --> 00:26:26,337
You better fix yourself.

381
00:26:26,362 --> 00:26:28,948
You're getting too old for that.

382
00:26:31,576 --> 00:26:33,119
But seriously, Bestie.

383
00:26:33,786 --> 00:26:35,913
It's endgame if they're getting married.

384
00:26:36,163 --> 00:26:37,123
Hey!

385
00:26:37,124 --> 00:26:38,541
What the are you talking about?!

386
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:41,460
Get a grip, Aya!

387
00:26:41,794 --> 00:26:43,379
But seriously, Bestie,

388
00:26:43,524 --> 00:26:45,734
DrAlys 'til the end of time!

389
00:26:46,299 --> 00:26:47,549
Really?

390
00:26:47,574 --> 00:26:49,034
I don't believe you.

391
00:26:49,643 --> 00:26:50,768
Didn't you say recently,

392
00:26:50,793 --> 00:26:53,420
"Wow, Tripp's so handsome!"

393
00:26:53,475 --> 00:26:55,978
And now it's "DrAlys forever!"

394
00:26:56,100 --> 00:26:58,028
Seriously, Alys.

395
00:26:59,055 --> 00:27:00,432
What happens now?

396
00:27:01,450 --> 00:27:03,031
What do you mean,
what happens now?

397
00:27:06,016 --> 00:27:07,225
We broke up.

398
00:27:07,250 --> 00:27:08,250
Remember?

399
00:27:10,270 --> 00:27:13,106
Yeah, there has to be a reason.

400
00:27:14,869 --> 00:27:15,911
But...

401
00:27:17,163 --> 00:27:18,496
What's Drake's reason?

402
00:27:18,497 --> 00:27:19,832
Do you know?

403
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,711
I don't know.

404
00:27:24,712 --> 00:27:27,506
And I don't want to know.

405
00:27:29,091 --> 00:27:30,884
Alys!

406
00:27:30,885 --> 00:27:32,345
You should ask him!

407
00:27:34,013 --> 00:27:35,765
I don't want to!

408
00:27:36,515 --> 00:27:37,642
I don't want to!

409
00:27:40,394 --> 00:27:41,729
Listen to me, Alys.

410
00:27:42,647 --> 00:27:43,814
Once and for all,

411
00:27:44,190 --> 00:27:45,566
ask him!

412
00:27:45,858 --> 00:27:48,027
Alys Zyril Ferrer Perez!

413
00:27:48,694 --> 00:27:49,737
Ask him!

414
00:27:49,862 --> 00:27:52,121
And if you still don't
want to be with him,

415
00:27:52,146 --> 00:27:53,522
I'll shut up for life!

416
00:27:54,492 --> 00:27:55,701
Aya!

417
00:27:58,871 --> 00:28:00,331
Tripp is a good man.

418
00:28:00,706 --> 00:28:02,500
Can't I just choose him instead?

419
00:28:02,958 --> 00:28:04,752
Can't I just be with him instead?

420
00:28:06,212 --> 00:28:07,254
Yeah.

421
00:28:08,130 --> 00:28:09,340
You and Tripp,

422
00:28:09,767 --> 00:28:11,027
good together.

423
00:28:12,343 --> 00:28:13,385
But Bestie,

424
00:28:13,386 --> 00:28:14,386
Bestie!

425
00:28:14,891 --> 00:28:15,976
You and Drake,

426
00:28:16,305 --> 00:28:18,432
Epic together!

427
00:28:19,467 --> 00:28:21,301
Bestie, you might have
gotten me sick, too.

428
00:28:21,326 --> 00:28:22,994
- Sorry, bestie.
- And that's the truth!

429
00:28:23,019 --> 00:28:24,061
Sorry, bestie.

430
00:28:30,528 --> 00:28:31,779
Yeah.

431
00:28:33,066 --> 00:28:35,722
We were epic when
we were together.

432
00:28:37,535 --> 00:28:38,777
We had our time.

433
00:28:40,235 --> 00:28:43,280
So, now,

434
00:28:44,375 --> 00:28:46,043
are you going to talk to him?

435
00:28:59,223 --> 00:29:01,725
Fine, yes.
Whatever.

436
00:29:01,726 --> 00:29:03,435
Good answer, Bestie!

437
00:29:03,436 --> 00:29:05,145
Okay, hold on, I'll call him.

438
00:29:05,146 --> 00:29:06,354
Stay there, wait.

439
00:29:06,355 --> 00:29:07,665
- Huh?!
- He’s downstairs.

440
00:29:07,690 --> 00:29:08,773
I’ll just call him.

441
00:29:08,774 --> 00:29:10,568
What do you mean “I'll call him”?

442
00:29:12,129 --> 00:29:13,277
Hey!

443
00:29:13,738 --> 00:29:15,656
Aya!

444
00:29:23,181 --> 00:29:24,582
It's okay, Alys.

445
00:29:24,607 --> 00:29:26,108
Everything will be alright.

446
00:29:41,348 --> 00:29:42,516
Drake?

447
00:29:52,902 --> 00:29:54,069
Talk.

448
00:29:56,947 --> 00:29:58,964
It’s because you made me
your whole world

449
00:29:59,450 --> 00:30:01,214
back then, Alys.

450
00:30:19,553 --> 00:30:20,638
That's it?

451
00:30:25,351 --> 00:30:27,102
No complicated shit?

452
00:30:30,439 --> 00:30:32,817
No mind-bending reason?

453
00:30:35,736 --> 00:30:38,239
Not even an implausible excuse?

454
00:30:39,657 --> 00:30:40,657
That’s it?

455
00:30:41,468 --> 00:30:42,885
Just plain...

456
00:30:42,910 --> 00:30:46,831
"I can't keep a love life and keep
living my life at the same time?"

457
00:30:48,415 --> 00:30:50,041
That's crap.

458
00:30:50,042 --> 00:30:51,126
That's it?

459
00:30:52,169 --> 00:30:54,088
It’s not only that, Alys.

460
00:30:57,234 --> 00:31:00,183
I left you because you were
ruining your life over me.

461
00:31:05,787 --> 00:31:09,121
You don't get to decide
what's good for me, Drake!

462
00:31:10,646 --> 00:31:12,106
Back then, I could.

463
00:31:14,955 --> 00:31:16,999
I was your boyfriend, Alys.

464
00:31:19,864 --> 00:31:21,152
And I knew,

465
00:31:21,987 --> 00:31:24,605
that we'd ruin each other
if we stayed that way.

466
00:31:25,119 --> 00:31:28,285
It wasn't worth it when you
had so much ahead of you.

467
00:31:28,998 --> 00:31:30,582
I wasn't pulling shits!

468
00:31:31,083 --> 00:31:32,519
What is this about?

469
00:31:32,615 --> 00:31:34,075
My studies?

470
00:31:35,681 --> 00:31:37,246
News flash.

471
00:31:37,663 --> 00:31:40,122
I was never smart,

472
00:31:40,342 --> 00:31:41,719
Mr. Genius.

473
00:31:42,462 --> 00:31:45,882
You think leaving me would
magically make me smart?

474
00:31:47,057 --> 00:31:48,057
It didn't.

475
00:31:52,062 --> 00:31:53,439
I dropped out.

476
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:55,816
Did you know that, Drake?

477
00:31:56,650 --> 00:31:58,986
Did you know what
you put me through?

478
00:32:10,873 --> 00:32:12,499
You were my boyfriend!

479
00:32:14,668 --> 00:32:16,253
Weren't you?!

480
00:32:17,254 --> 00:32:19,380
You were supposed to be the one

481
00:32:19,381 --> 00:32:22,051
helping and encouraging me to study!

482
00:32:25,262 --> 00:32:26,819
I was in New York.

483
00:32:28,692 --> 00:32:31,445
I was alone.
I barely knew anyone.

484
00:32:32,353 --> 00:32:34,256
Shit, I’ve never

485
00:32:34,563 --> 00:32:37,858
felt so alone.

486
00:32:39,610 --> 00:32:41,111
Only then, Drake.

487
00:32:42,237 --> 00:32:43,656
Wherever I'd look,

488
00:32:43,989 --> 00:32:45,782
I couldn't recognize anyone.

489
00:32:45,783 --> 00:32:47,493
I couldn't talk to anyone.

490
00:32:47,905 --> 00:32:49,531
Drake, I was so

491
00:32:49,857 --> 00:32:51,233
fucking lonely.

492
00:32:53,874 --> 00:32:55,376
Do you remember?

493
00:32:56,669 --> 00:32:59,296
The day I left on that rooftop?

494
00:33:00,506 --> 00:33:02,132
Do you know

495
00:33:02,466 --> 00:33:06,136
how badly I wanted you

496
00:33:08,897 --> 00:33:10,524
to stop me?

497
00:33:12,768 --> 00:33:14,520
"Alys, don't go."

498
00:33:17,773 --> 00:33:20,401
That's all I wanted to hear.

499
00:33:23,696 --> 00:33:24,989
That's all.

500
00:33:26,740 --> 00:33:28,283
Three words.

501
00:33:28,909 --> 00:33:30,661
Ten letters.

502
00:33:31,704 --> 00:33:33,956
But you didn't even give me that.

503
00:33:39,424 --> 00:33:41,301
Did you even know that, Drake?

504
00:33:42,423 --> 00:33:45,932
I loved you so fucking much!

505
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:51,042
To the point that I begged
my parents to let me stay!

506
00:33:53,934 --> 00:33:55,174
Did you know that?

507
00:33:56,228 --> 00:33:57,771
What do you know about me?

508
00:34:00,149 --> 00:34:01,733
All you ever knew

509
00:34:01,734 --> 00:34:04,068
was Alys Zyril Perez,

510
00:34:04,069 --> 00:34:06,279
who tried so hard

511
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:07,906
to be your girlfriend.

512
00:34:09,116 --> 00:34:10,743
Now that I've mentioned it,

513
00:34:13,037 --> 00:34:14,246
I feel so cheap.

514
00:34:17,299 --> 00:34:20,172
That's what you must think of me.

515
00:34:21,378 --> 00:34:23,140
A little dog!

516
00:34:24,365 --> 00:34:26,451
I was like a dog!

517
00:34:27,259 --> 00:34:28,594
Following you around.

518
00:34:29,511 --> 00:34:32,056
Shit, I wait for your
fucking command.

519
00:34:36,060 --> 00:34:39,229
Is that why it was easy
to take me for granted?

520
00:34:40,275 --> 00:34:41,531
Because you know what,

521
00:34:43,025 --> 00:34:45,140
whatever you did,

522
00:34:46,737 --> 00:34:48,828
even if you did nothing,

523
00:34:50,616 --> 00:34:52,289
I would be there.

524
00:34:53,869 --> 00:34:56,497
I loved you over and over again, Drake!

525
00:34:57,581 --> 00:35:00,667
I loved you over and over again, Drake!

526
00:35:01,627 --> 00:35:04,379
I loved you over and over again, Drake!

527
00:35:09,843 --> 00:35:11,512
And you fucked me over.

528
00:35:13,347 --> 00:35:15,641
I was so easy to
leave behind, wasn't I?

529
00:35:16,767 --> 00:35:20,184
That was the reason you left me?
What the fucking hell!

530
00:35:22,999 --> 00:35:24,739
You’re so funny!

531
00:35:28,259 --> 00:35:29,552
I love you.

532
00:35:32,923 --> 00:35:34,216
There.

533
00:35:35,035 --> 00:35:36,122
There it is.

534
00:35:37,121 --> 00:35:40,122
Every time he's like this,
I lose myself.

535
00:35:42,125 --> 00:35:43,668
But I don't want this anymore.

536
00:35:46,421 --> 00:35:47,589
Please.

537
00:35:47,714 --> 00:35:48,882
Enough.

538
00:35:50,676 --> 00:35:51,927
Are you finished, Alys?

539
00:35:54,179 --> 00:35:55,305
No, Drake.

540
00:35:56,932 --> 00:36:00,301
I'll never be finished with you.
And you'll never hear the end of it.

541
00:36:01,895 --> 00:36:02,980
Good.

542
00:36:04,559 --> 00:36:08,605
Because I couldn't care less
about whatever you say, Alys.

543
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:12,338
As long as you speak to me,
I'll be happy.

544
00:36:31,175 --> 00:36:32,325
Don't cry.

545
00:36:45,522 --> 00:36:46,544
Talk.

546
00:36:48,358 --> 00:36:49,985
I'd rather not, Alys.

547
00:36:50,652 --> 00:36:53,655
Because every time I talk,
you always cry.

548
00:36:54,774 --> 00:36:56,357
When you talk,

549
00:36:56,491 --> 00:36:57,492
I listen.

550
00:36:57,868 --> 00:36:59,098
When I talk,

551
00:36:59,979 --> 00:37:00,980
you cry.

552
00:37:01,663 --> 00:37:02,706
So, I'd rather not.

553
00:37:03,665 --> 00:37:04,708
Fine.

554
00:37:04,903 --> 00:37:06,280
That's how it is, Drake.

555
00:37:09,296 --> 00:37:10,778
Are you mad, too?

556
00:37:13,091 --> 00:37:16,512
Because I am really fucking mad.

557
00:37:19,034 --> 00:37:20,872
Drake, talk.

558
00:37:23,862 --> 00:37:25,122
Stop crying.

559
00:37:25,729 --> 00:37:27,105
Please, Alys.

560
00:37:33,528 --> 00:37:37,032
You don't get to decide
for me now, Drake.

561
00:37:37,437 --> 00:37:39,528
You're not my boyfriend anymore.

562
00:37:41,036 --> 00:37:42,704
I know.

563
00:37:45,016 --> 00:37:47,239
But I love you so much, Alys.

564
00:37:47,368 --> 00:37:48,536
I loved you then,

565
00:37:49,586 --> 00:37:50,754
until now.

566
00:37:52,422 --> 00:37:53,882
You just haven't accepted it.

567
00:37:54,716 --> 00:37:56,676
Or you just don't want to.

568
00:38:00,097 --> 00:38:01,504
Please, Drake.

569
00:38:03,225 --> 00:38:04,215
Please...

570
00:38:06,728 --> 00:38:08,814
Stop saying that you love me.

571
00:38:09,690 --> 00:38:10,919
I love Tripp.

572
00:38:25,325 --> 00:38:27,244
I'm still in love with you, Alys.

573
00:38:29,251 --> 00:38:30,251
Always.

574
00:38:31,795 --> 00:38:32,795
Always.

575
00:38:35,048 --> 00:38:37,801
You always call me selfish.

576
00:38:39,678 --> 00:38:41,680
But, Alys, how was that selfish?

577
00:38:42,134 --> 00:38:44,372
I put your well being first,

578
00:38:44,566 --> 00:38:46,443
before my own feelings.

579
00:38:51,143 --> 00:38:52,575
I did everything I could

580
00:38:52,899 --> 00:38:55,276
to stay in your life.

581
00:38:55,728 --> 00:38:57,622
Even when we were apart,

582
00:38:57,779 --> 00:38:59,489
I tried to follow you.

583
00:39:11,460 --> 00:39:13,231
But the more I watch you,

584
00:39:15,297 --> 00:39:17,434
there’s one thing
I can’t accept.

585
00:39:23,805 --> 00:39:27,528
You're slowly ruining
your life because of me.

586
00:39:30,171 --> 00:39:33,770
I couldn't bear to watch.
Because I love you.

587
00:39:36,234 --> 00:39:37,559
I love you so much.

588
00:39:42,224 --> 00:39:43,559
Alys.

589
00:39:47,037 --> 00:39:51,040
I can love you without
forgetting about myself.

590
00:39:51,041 --> 00:39:52,041
You can't.

591
00:39:54,336 --> 00:39:55,796
I can.

592
00:39:57,631 --> 00:39:58,757
No, Alys.

593
00:40:02,386 --> 00:40:05,514
And every time you
try to choose me,

594
00:40:07,140 --> 00:40:09,684
there’s one thing you always forget.

595
00:40:11,228 --> 00:40:13,563
I can't bear to watch that, Alys.

596
00:40:15,649 --> 00:40:16,900
Fuck you, Drake!

597
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:22,489
All I did was fucking love you!

598
00:40:24,282 --> 00:40:27,702
I just loved you!
What was so wrong with that?

599
00:40:30,622 --> 00:40:32,791
All I did was love you!

600
00:40:33,667 --> 00:40:36,086
In your eyes,
all you did was love me.

601
00:40:37,337 --> 00:40:38,672
The way I see it,

602
00:40:39,297 --> 00:40:41,425
you're forgetting who you are.

603
00:40:42,843 --> 00:40:44,511
Are you saying,

604
00:40:45,804 --> 00:40:47,763
that I was destroying my life

605
00:40:47,764 --> 00:40:49,724
when I was dating you?

606
00:40:51,101 --> 00:40:52,310
No, Drake.

607
00:40:52,894 --> 00:40:55,772
Get this through your thick head!

608
00:40:59,234 --> 00:41:00,360
You...

609
00:41:02,863 --> 00:41:05,198
You broke me when you
left me in New York!

610
00:41:08,493 --> 00:41:10,495
I didn't break myself.

611
00:41:13,248 --> 00:41:14,248
You did!

612
00:41:14,316 --> 00:41:15,363
No, Alys.

613
00:41:17,848 --> 00:41:20,434
I stopped you
from destroying yourself.

614
00:41:22,632 --> 00:41:23,989
Listen to me, Alys.

615
00:41:25,927 --> 00:41:27,637
I never ever asked

616
00:41:28,656 --> 00:41:31,117
that you love me at
the cost of your life.

617
00:41:35,729 --> 00:41:37,272
I'd never ask you

618
00:41:39,107 --> 00:41:40,567
to choose me.

619
00:41:41,818 --> 00:41:43,862
If someone has to do the chasing,

620
00:41:44,738 --> 00:41:45,864
let it be me.

621
00:41:47,532 --> 00:41:50,285
If someone has to wait,

622
00:41:51,578 --> 00:41:52,787
let it be me.

623
00:41:53,955 --> 00:41:56,374
If someone has to get hurt,

624
00:41:57,501 --> 00:41:58,710
let it be me, Alys.

625
00:42:07,677 --> 00:42:08,887
No, Drake.

626
00:42:09,471 --> 00:42:10,471
That's enough.

627
00:42:12,349 --> 00:42:14,518
Alys, I will wait for you

628
00:42:15,727 --> 00:42:18,063
if you tell me to.

629
00:42:18,563 --> 00:42:20,899
I'm willing to love you, Alys,

630
00:42:22,025 --> 00:42:24,861
while you're living your best life.

631
00:42:26,196 --> 00:42:28,240
I'm willing to be the fool, Alys.

632
00:42:33,411 --> 00:42:34,788
Just say yes.

633
00:42:35,497 --> 00:42:37,229
Please say yes, Alys.

634
00:42:39,026 --> 00:42:40,643
I'm begging you.

635
00:42:43,022 --> 00:42:45,066
I'll be waiting, Alys.

636
00:42:47,592 --> 00:42:48,885
I'll be waiting.

637
00:42:51,054 --> 00:42:53,135
I can handle the pain.

638
00:42:53,160 --> 00:42:56,289
And I can give you all my love.

639
00:42:57,443 --> 00:42:58,945
I'll wait for you, Alys.

640
00:43:01,106 --> 00:43:03,400
Just give me a chance.

641
00:44:03,608 --> 00:44:06,403
It's been three days
since I talked to Drake.

642
00:44:06,869 --> 00:44:08,079
And I haven't slept.

643
00:44:08,365 --> 00:44:09,825
I've been avoiding Tripp, too.

644
00:44:10,060 --> 00:44:12,271
Shit, I feel so guilty.

645
00:44:12,852 --> 00:44:14,937
It feels like I'm playing with them.

646
00:44:15,513 --> 00:44:17,057
I know I shouldn't.

647
00:44:17,152 --> 00:44:17,903
Hey!

648
00:44:17,928 --> 00:44:18,970
What happened to you?

649
00:44:20,897 --> 00:44:21,814
Nothing.

650
00:44:21,839 --> 00:44:24,382
I'm a little stressed about
Drake and Cristine's wedding.

651
00:44:27,692 --> 00:44:28,777
What?

652
00:44:29,170 --> 00:44:30,588
What is it now?

653
00:44:31,109 --> 00:44:32,272
Tell me the truth, Alys.

654
00:44:33,698 --> 00:44:35,033
Do you need a handout?

655
00:44:35,825 --> 00:44:37,661
And what makes you think that?

656
00:44:38,682 --> 00:44:39,683
Well,

657
00:44:41,206 --> 00:44:42,582
it's just a thought. Because...

658
00:44:43,249 --> 00:44:44,241
Think about it.

659
00:44:44,834 --> 00:44:46,418
Why would you choose

660
00:44:46,419 --> 00:44:49,046
to be the wedding planner
for your own ex?

661
00:44:49,047 --> 00:44:50,047
Right?

662
00:44:50,230 --> 00:44:51,230
Of course.

663
00:44:52,006 --> 00:44:54,383
It's the only explanation
I thought of. It’s either...

664
00:44:54,886 --> 00:44:56,554
You're broke,

665
00:44:57,180 --> 00:44:58,807
or a real masochist.

666
00:44:59,224 --> 00:45:01,059
I have my reasons, okay?

667
00:45:01,810 --> 00:45:03,269
It's none of your business.

668
00:45:03,353 --> 00:45:04,479
Whatever you say.

669
00:45:05,188 --> 00:45:06,480
But Alys,

670
00:45:06,481 --> 00:45:08,148
get it together.

671
00:45:08,149 --> 00:45:08,942
You know,

672
00:45:08,943 --> 00:45:10,109
one of these days,

673
00:45:10,110 --> 00:45:12,987
one of those two brain
cells is going to give out.

674
00:45:14,614 --> 00:45:15,824
That's harsh.

675
00:45:17,617 --> 00:45:19,661
Oh, Alys!

676
00:45:19,869 --> 00:45:21,995
Since you're the wedding planner...

677
00:45:21,996 --> 00:45:22,849
Yeah?

678
00:45:22,874 --> 00:45:24,165
Could I

679
00:45:24,190 --> 00:45:25,566
get an invitation?

680
00:45:25,775 --> 00:45:26,401
Why?

681
00:45:26,426 --> 00:45:27,801
You weren't invited?

682
00:45:28,268 --> 00:45:31,103
You know that me and Drake
are basically Tom and Jerry.

683
00:45:31,128 --> 00:45:31,629
Right?

684
00:45:31,699 --> 00:45:32,699
Of course, I wasn't.

685
00:45:33,379 --> 00:45:34,379
Come on!

686
00:45:34,667 --> 00:45:36,419
Squeeze me into the guest list.

687
00:45:37,971 --> 00:45:39,560
Okay, but...

688
00:45:40,346 --> 00:45:41,305
But?

689
00:45:41,330 --> 00:45:43,873
Tell me why Drake
is so mad at you.

690
00:45:45,910 --> 00:45:47,412
In your dreams, Perez.

691
00:45:48,898 --> 00:45:49,898
Okay!

692
00:45:49,899 --> 00:45:51,357
Then no invites for you.

693
00:45:51,382 --> 00:45:53,051
You'll just have to crash it.

694
00:45:53,752 --> 00:45:54,803
Whatever.

695
00:45:55,219 --> 00:45:56,846
But I do have a question.

696
00:45:57,263 --> 00:45:57,972
Hmm?

697
00:45:57,997 --> 00:46:00,374
Is Drake’s wedding real or...

698
00:46:01,009 --> 00:46:02,009
just a scam?

699
00:46:02,753 --> 00:46:04,630
Why would it be a scam?

700
00:46:05,617 --> 00:46:06,952
To tell you honestly,

701
00:46:07,198 --> 00:46:09,032
no one in the family knows

702
00:46:09,087 --> 00:46:10,921
that a wedding is about to happen.

703
00:46:10,946 --> 00:46:11,530
What?!

704
00:46:11,814 --> 00:46:13,654
What? Explain it clearly!

705
00:46:14,349 --> 00:46:15,557
Just relax, okay?

706
00:46:15,582 --> 00:46:16,667
Spit it out!

707
00:46:16,694 --> 00:46:17,737
The thing is...

708
00:46:18,178 --> 00:46:19,928
I asked Mom, Dad

709
00:46:19,953 --> 00:46:21,092
and even grandma.

710
00:46:21,590 --> 00:46:23,425
Nobody's heard of a wedding!

711
00:46:23,620 --> 00:46:25,456
They even thought it was a prank!

712
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:28,670
And did you know...

713
00:46:29,814 --> 00:46:31,106
Know what?!

714
00:46:31,232 --> 00:46:32,066
Spit it out!

715
00:46:32,067 --> 00:46:33,735
Enough with the suspense already!

716
00:46:33,860 --> 00:46:34,860
So, here's the thing.

717
00:46:35,945 --> 00:46:37,405
When I asked grandma,

718
00:46:37,824 --> 00:46:39,283
all she said was...

719
00:46:39,308 --> 00:46:40,308
“Drake?”

720
00:46:40,799 --> 00:46:43,759
“I don't know anything
about a wedding, dear.”

721
00:46:43,838 --> 00:46:46,174
“All I know is what Steve told me.”

722
00:46:46,237 --> 00:46:49,907
“Drake's just waiting for
his girlfriend who's abroad.”

723
00:46:50,502 --> 00:46:51,795
Don't you get it?

724
00:46:52,087 --> 00:46:54,297
Jeez, thank god Tripp wasn't there!

725
00:46:54,881 --> 00:46:56,341
If he was there? Well...

726
00:46:56,366 --> 00:46:59,077
It'd be World War II in the Palma family.

727
00:46:59,886 --> 00:47:01,303
No, Alys.

728
00:47:01,304 --> 00:47:04,056
You're not the only girl who went abroad.

729
00:47:04,057 --> 00:47:05,682
Don't assume.

730
00:47:05,683 --> 00:47:07,643
But, damn,

731
00:47:07,644 --> 00:47:10,604
stop lying to yourself, Alys.

732
00:47:10,605 --> 00:47:13,256
You're clearly the one Drake
was talking about.

733
00:47:14,484 --> 00:47:16,653
Drake and his crooked world.

734
00:47:17,498 --> 00:47:18,415
You know,

735
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:22,694
I always thought it was Shaira
those two were fighting over.

736
00:47:23,294 --> 00:47:24,420
Turns out it was just you.

737
00:47:26,184 --> 00:47:28,854
How about sending some
of that beauty, Perez?

738
00:47:29,323 --> 00:47:30,573
I’ll really kill him!

739
00:47:30,598 --> 00:47:32,391
Hey, just relax!

740
00:47:32,416 --> 00:47:33,709
That's expensive!

741
00:47:43,079 --> 00:47:47,083
Charmaine, don't forget
about the 2:00 PM delivery.

742
00:47:48,810 --> 00:47:49,810
Bestie!

743
00:47:50,728 --> 00:47:53,689
- Bestie!
- Bestie!

744
00:47:53,690 --> 00:47:56,250
You know, this is the first time
I've seen you at Mom's boutique.

745
00:47:56,275 --> 00:47:57,652
I thought you’re
a ghost employee.

746
00:47:57,902 --> 00:47:58,902
Whatever.

747
00:48:00,572 --> 00:48:02,073
What are you doing here, anyway?

748
00:48:03,241 --> 00:48:05,242
Well, I'm here to pick up
Ms. Stinson's gown.

749
00:48:05,243 --> 00:48:06,786
I'm taking it to Batangas.

750
00:48:07,273 --> 00:48:08,900
Wedding's in a few days.

751
00:48:09,210 --> 00:48:09,960
My god.

752
00:48:09,985 --> 00:48:12,403
You'll forever be the martyr.

753
00:48:12,883 --> 00:48:14,468
I don't know what to do with you.

754
00:48:14,641 --> 00:48:15,682
Gosh.

755
00:48:15,707 --> 00:48:18,251
Weren't you the one
pushing me and Drake to talk?

756
00:48:18,276 --> 00:48:21,195
And now you're going
on about me being a martyr?

757
00:48:21,897 --> 00:48:22,815
Ms. Alys!

758
00:48:22,840 --> 00:48:25,508
Both the gown and the
mannequin are in your car, Ma'am.

759
00:48:25,533 --> 00:48:26,768
Okay, thank you!

760
00:48:27,241 --> 00:48:28,533
Bestie,

761
00:48:28,558 --> 00:48:30,517
let's get an early lunch, first.

762
00:48:30,518 --> 00:48:31,853
Oh, no. I can't, Bestie.

763
00:48:32,270 --> 00:48:33,187
I'm leaving right now,

764
00:48:33,188 --> 00:48:37,065
because an early lunch
with you will last all evening.

765
00:48:37,066 --> 00:48:38,358
I know you too well.

766
00:48:38,359 --> 00:48:41,778
If I let you gossip,
I'll never be able to leave.

767
00:48:41,779 --> 00:48:43,614
What about early dinner instead?

768
00:48:43,615 --> 00:48:45,575
- Don't you want to hear the tea?
- Oh, late dinner?

769
00:48:46,326 --> 00:48:47,494
I do.

770
00:48:48,536 --> 00:48:49,746
My gosh.

771
00:48:50,163 --> 00:48:51,788
- Why?
- Gosh, so annoying.

772
00:48:51,789 --> 00:48:53,958
Are you going out with Kent?

773
00:48:54,876 --> 00:48:57,169
Are you getting back together with.

774
00:48:57,170 --> 00:48:59,171
"Bee!"

775
00:48:59,172 --> 00:49:00,589
"Bee!"

776
00:49:00,590 --> 00:49:02,507
- "Bee!"
- Bestie, that’s enough.

777
00:49:02,508 --> 00:49:05,052
Just go already. That’s right, go!

778
00:49:05,053 --> 00:49:06,638
"Bee!"

779
00:49:06,888 --> 00:49:07,847
I'll be going now.

780
00:49:07,848 --> 00:49:09,408
- Bye, Bestie! I love you.
- You’re crazy.

781
00:49:09,599 --> 00:49:11,642
"Bee!"

782
00:49:11,643 --> 00:49:14,561
My bestie!

783
00:49:14,562 --> 00:49:16,314
Is she crazy?

784
00:49:30,728 --> 00:49:32,479
I asked Mom, Dad

785
00:49:32,504 --> 00:49:33,729
and even grandma.

786
00:49:34,164 --> 00:49:35,708
Nobody's heard of a wedding!

787
00:49:36,141 --> 00:49:38,184
They even thought it was a prank!

788
00:49:39,170 --> 00:49:41,297
What is that Tofer talking about?

789
00:49:42,416 --> 00:49:45,586
I've invested too much into
this for it to be a fake wedding.

790
00:49:46,695 --> 00:49:48,404
What is this then?

791
00:49:48,429 --> 00:49:50,098
What is it for?

792
00:50:12,036 --> 00:50:13,036
Hi, Silly!

793
00:50:13,061 --> 00:50:14,313
Anything interesting?

794
00:50:18,084 --> 00:50:19,084
Hey!

795
00:50:19,109 --> 00:50:20,736
Are we getting married now, Perez?

796
00:50:20,761 --> 00:50:22,012
What's with the wedding gown?

797
00:50:26,886 --> 00:50:28,604
I'll wait for you, Alys.

798
00:50:29,280 --> 00:50:31,782
Just give me a chance.

799
00:50:44,360 --> 00:50:46,154
You're the worst, Alys.

800
00:50:49,532 --> 00:50:52,285
How could you do this to him?

801
00:51:08,051 --> 00:51:09,037
Tripp.

802
00:51:10,094 --> 00:51:11,137
Zy?

803
00:51:11,345 --> 00:51:12,972
Tripp, I'm so sorry.

804
00:51:13,811 --> 00:51:15,187
I'm so sorry, Tripp.

805
00:51:15,683 --> 00:51:16,683
What?

806
00:51:16,934 --> 00:51:17,977
What do you mean, sorry?

807
00:51:19,395 --> 00:51:21,318
I love you, okay?

808
00:51:22,565 --> 00:51:23,899
What?!

809
00:51:23,900 --> 00:51:25,318
What are you talking about?

810
00:51:26,069 --> 00:51:27,153
What-

811
00:51:30,782 --> 00:51:32,992
I hate to tell it to your face, Tripp.

812
00:51:34,597 --> 00:51:36,286
You don’t deserve this.

813
00:51:48,424 --> 00:51:51,259
My god!
I missed the Philippines!

814
00:51:51,260 --> 00:51:52,803
But I didn't miss you, Drake.

815
00:51:52,804 --> 00:51:54,180
You're still so ugly.

816
00:51:54,847 --> 00:51:55,932
Stupid.

817
00:51:56,974 --> 00:51:58,601
What do you mean, stupid?

818
00:51:59,727 --> 00:52:02,312
And here I was doing you a favor!

819
00:52:02,313 --> 00:52:04,653
You know I hate flying to Canada.

820
00:52:04,784 --> 00:52:06,077
But I did it for you.

821
00:52:07,360 --> 00:52:09,320
Fine, thank you.

822
00:52:10,279 --> 00:52:11,947
Now, you’re thanking me.

823
00:52:11,948 --> 00:52:13,449
You're annoying.

824
00:52:13,767 --> 00:52:15,519
Why did you go to Canada though?

825
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:17,830
You should have gone
to the other place, then.

826
00:52:17,855 --> 00:52:18,805
Stupid.

827
00:52:18,830 --> 00:52:20,747
Ugh! The nerve!

828
00:52:20,748 --> 00:52:21,415
Ingrate!

829
00:52:21,415 --> 00:52:22,333
Tattletale!

830
00:52:22,333 --> 00:52:23,251
Bastard!

831
00:52:23,251 --> 00:52:24,251
Flirt.

832
00:52:24,408 --> 00:52:25,408
No, I'm not!

833
00:52:25,670 --> 00:52:26,395
Oh!

834
00:52:26,420 --> 00:52:27,387
I almost forgot.

835
00:52:27,421 --> 00:52:28,881
I met someone over there.

836
00:52:29,361 --> 00:52:30,361
Her name's Fier.

837
00:52:30,566 --> 00:52:32,276
She's so pretty!

838
00:52:33,302 --> 00:52:36,389
I invited her to take a vacation
here in the Philippines.

839
00:52:37,140 --> 00:52:40,767
If you want, I'll introduce you
so you'll have another friend.

840
00:52:40,768 --> 00:52:41,561
No.

841
00:52:41,562 --> 00:52:43,980
Just shut up.
That would be so much better.

842
00:52:44,355 --> 00:52:45,773
You're so grumpy.

843
00:52:46,691 --> 00:52:47,774
Oh, wait.

844
00:52:47,775 --> 00:52:48,860
Where's the gown?

845
00:52:55,116 --> 00:52:56,700
Is this really the gown?!

846
00:52:56,701 --> 00:52:59,494
Oh my god! It's so pretty!

847
00:52:59,495 --> 00:53:02,415
You'll drop dead when
you see Alys in this!

848
00:53:03,339 --> 00:53:05,258
She's always beautiful.

849
00:53:05,752 --> 00:53:06,586
Idiot.

850
00:53:06,611 --> 00:53:07,903
You can't pull that off.

851
00:53:09,086 --> 00:53:10,253
But that's good.

852
00:53:10,715 --> 00:53:11,883
Improving.

853
00:53:12,622 --> 00:53:13,926
You're not stoic anymore.

854
00:53:14,510 --> 00:53:15,636
Just a little.

855
00:53:17,180 --> 00:53:18,847
Please, please...

856
00:53:18,848 --> 00:53:20,391
What the hell is happening?

857
00:53:20,823 --> 00:53:23,366
I want to call out and
ask them, but I can't.

858
00:53:23,391 --> 00:53:25,602
I'm afraid of what I'll find out.

859
00:53:26,230 --> 00:53:27,690
All these things...

860
00:53:28,274 --> 00:53:29,274
Damn it!

861
00:53:29,337 --> 00:53:30,755
It all makes sense now.

862
00:53:31,277 --> 00:53:32,945
The gown, the place...

863
00:53:33,279 --> 00:53:36,324
The fact that the Palmas don't
know he's getting married.

864
00:53:36,657 --> 00:53:39,202
How everyone still
thinks I'm his girlfriend.

865
00:53:40,036 --> 00:53:42,663
All the chasing and the screaming.

866
00:53:42,747 --> 00:53:44,458
Drake...

867
00:53:44,874 --> 00:53:47,084
I just wish your plan doesn't backfire.

868
00:53:48,586 --> 00:53:49,921
I mean,

869
00:53:50,379 --> 00:53:51,505
I've done my part,

870
00:53:52,089 --> 00:53:53,216
you did your begging.

871
00:53:54,675 --> 00:53:56,260
Now it's up to Alys.

872
00:53:56,950 --> 00:53:59,013
If she'll say, yes.

873
00:53:59,597 --> 00:54:02,266
And I do hope she'll say yes.

874
00:54:05,478 --> 00:54:07,980
Wait. When's the proposal?

875
00:54:10,483 --> 00:54:12,025
Damn this life.

876
00:54:12,026 --> 00:54:14,945
It's only been a month since I got back.

877
00:54:14,946 --> 00:54:17,365
But I've gone through so much already.

878
00:54:17,990 --> 00:54:20,117
I wish I'd never come back.

879
00:54:23,537 --> 00:54:24,997
The day before the wedding.

880
00:54:27,166 --> 00:54:29,084
Okay, well...

881
00:54:29,085 --> 00:54:30,461
What if she doesn't accept?

882
00:54:38,302 --> 00:54:39,302
She will.

883
00:54:40,012 --> 00:54:41,054
Whoa!

884
00:54:41,055 --> 00:54:42,890
Somebody's got confidence.

885
00:54:43,599 --> 00:54:44,812
Go, Drake.

886
00:54:45,309 --> 00:54:46,519
Shut up.

887
00:54:47,812 --> 00:54:50,356
I know Alys will say yes.

888
00:54:53,943 --> 00:54:54,943
What —.

889
00:54:54,944 --> 00:54:57,071
Think, Alys, think!

890
00:55:18,305 --> 00:55:19,811
Thank you, Nanny.

891
00:55:38,029 --> 00:55:39,038
Oh!

892
00:55:39,613 --> 00:55:42,533
So it's true.
You've been chasing Alys.

893
00:55:45,828 --> 00:55:47,621
What are you planning, Drake?

894
00:55:48,581 --> 00:55:50,750
To hurt my best friend again?

895
00:55:54,253 --> 00:55:55,880
I want us to get back together.

896
00:55:57,277 --> 00:55:58,360
Now?

897
00:55:58,385 --> 00:55:59,553
Why?

898
00:56:00,051 --> 00:56:02,219
After everything,
you suddenly want her again?

899
00:56:04,138 --> 00:56:05,556
You really are something.

900
00:56:06,599 --> 00:56:07,683
What do you think this is?

901
00:56:08,768 --> 00:56:10,394
Highschool all over again?

902
00:56:10,644 --> 00:56:11,937
Nothing's changed, Aya.

903
00:56:16,484 --> 00:56:17,777
I still love her.

904
00:56:18,361 --> 00:56:19,361
No, Drake.

905
00:56:19,700 --> 00:56:21,785
You don't hurt the person you love.

906
00:56:22,782 --> 00:56:24,992
Did you know I almost
put a hex on you?

907
00:56:25,743 --> 00:56:28,037
You hurt Alys!

908
00:56:28,454 --> 00:56:30,164
She barely survived!

909
00:56:31,582 --> 00:56:35,627
I was there!
I saw how hurt Alys was!

910
00:56:35,628 --> 00:56:37,088
My best friend!

911
00:56:38,714 --> 00:56:39,715
Maybe.

912
00:56:40,758 --> 00:56:42,551
But I had no choice.

913
00:56:43,552 --> 00:56:45,529
Are you insane, Drake Palma?

914
00:56:45,888 --> 00:56:46,972
Are you a sadist?!

915
00:56:47,598 --> 00:56:49,809
You say you love her
and then you hurt her?

916
00:56:50,129 --> 00:56:52,715
Aya, you know what
Alys is going through.

917
00:56:53,020 --> 00:56:55,355
She'd fail if I hadn't left her.

918
00:56:55,356 --> 00:56:57,233
I chose to be the villain.

919
00:56:57,900 --> 00:56:59,402
Rather than stop her from succeeding.

920
00:57:00,027 --> 00:57:01,779
She failed NYCU!

921
00:57:02,238 --> 00:57:03,114
She dropped out.

922
00:57:03,115 --> 00:57:04,490
And now she's successful.

923
00:57:04,740 --> 00:57:06,117
But in pain!

924
00:57:06,659 --> 00:57:08,160
Is that what you wanted, Drake?

925
00:57:08,369 --> 00:57:09,369
No.

926
00:57:10,037 --> 00:57:10,996
And you know that.

927
00:57:10,996 --> 00:57:11,996
Whatever!

928
00:57:13,541 --> 00:57:14,624
Stay there.

929
00:57:14,625 --> 00:57:15,459
I'll talk to her.

930
00:57:15,460 --> 00:57:16,836
Aya, do you think...

931
00:57:19,046 --> 00:57:20,423
That's her decision to make.

932
00:57:21,924 --> 00:57:24,009
Only she can know
if she still wants to.

933
00:57:26,345 --> 00:57:28,055
But one thing's for certain...

934
00:57:29,807 --> 00:57:31,641
What you did to her

935
00:57:31,642 --> 00:57:34,394
is something she'll never forget.

936
00:57:34,395 --> 00:57:36,564
Something she'll never forgive.

937
00:57:37,314 --> 00:57:39,629
I can only help so much.

938
00:57:40,359 --> 00:57:42,319
And don't even think of abusing my help.

939
00:57:43,696 --> 00:57:44,696
If you do,

940
00:57:44,864 --> 00:57:46,823
I'll make sure to put a hex on you.

941
00:57:46,824 --> 00:57:48,033
Stay there!

942
00:57:49,034 --> 00:57:50,035
Thank you, Aya.

943
00:57:53,823 --> 00:57:54,823
Drake.

944
00:58:00,457 --> 00:58:01,834
I am watching you.

945
00:58:03,632 --> 00:58:05,259
You reap what you sow.

946
00:58:20,774 --> 00:58:22,985
Dane, how's Bestie?

947
00:58:23,569 --> 00:58:25,154
I think she's better.

948
00:58:38,417 --> 00:58:39,627
Bestie!

949
00:58:39,877 --> 00:58:41,712
Who are you talking to, Bestie?

950
00:58:43,923 --> 00:58:47,468
On the next episode of
Dating Alys Perez.

951
00:58:53,224 --> 00:58:55,434
It hurts too much, Mommy.

952
00:58:55,663 --> 00:58:57,164
Is this about Drake again?

953
00:58:57,189 --> 00:58:59,191
Are you sure Alys is happy with you?

954
00:58:59,563 --> 00:59:00,815
I'm sorry!

955
00:59:01,524 --> 00:59:03,108
Would you like to know

956
00:59:03,567 --> 00:59:05,318
how she looks at me

957
00:59:05,319 --> 00:59:07,071
even when she's mad at me?

958
00:59:07,196 --> 00:59:08,196
Marco?!

959
00:59:08,447 --> 00:59:09,448
Motherfucker!

960
00:59:10,191 --> 00:59:11,871
- You fucking asshole!
- Alys still loves me.

961
00:59:12,258 --> 00:59:13,592
I can feel it, Tripp.

962
00:59:19,166 --> 00:59:20,250
- Alys.
- Alys.

963
00:59:20,251 --> 00:59:22,078
You two!
Just stop already!

964
00:59:22,169 --> 00:59:23,754
Give me a little space to breathe!

965
00:59:24,547 --> 00:59:25,673
Tripp?

966
00:59:26,465 --> 00:59:27,841
What happened to you?
